{"id":"1008.1533","submitter":"James Martin","authors":"J. D. Carter and J. D. D. Martin","title":"Energy shifts of Rydberg atoms due to patch fields near metal surfaces","comments":"7 pages, 2 figures, Revised version contains an illustrative scanning\n  electron microscope image","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. A, v. 83, 032902 (2011)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.83.032902","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.atom-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The statistical properties of patch electric fields due to a polycrystalline\nmetal surface are calculated. The fluctuations in the electric field scale like\n1/z^2, when z >> w, where z is the distance to the surface, and w is the\ncharacteristic length scale of the surface patches. For typical thermally\nevaporated gold surfaces these field fluctuations are comparable to the image\nfield of an elementary charge, and scale in the same way with distance to the\nsurface. Expressions for calculating the statistics of the inhomogeneous\nbroadening of Rydberg atom energies due to patch electric fields are presented.\nSpatial variations in the patch fields over the Rydberg orbit are found to be\ninsignificant.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Aug 2010 15:47:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 2 Jan 2011 01:19:18 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 7 Mar 2011 16:55:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-03-05"}
